{
 "name": "RPlog_Of_Ships_and_Sentients_Butchers_and_Arrivals_-_part_2",
 "title": "Of Ships and Sentients, Butchers and Arrivals (Part 2)",
 "summary": "At the elegant seaside restaurant Ruathen's Deep Blue Sea on Caspar, the doctor Lynae Cassius shares a wry, deeply philosophical conversation with HM743, a self-aware heavy-maintenance droid leased to the Caspian Navy, over questions of sentience, legal personhood, lifeform status, and self-deception. Their debate is interrupted by the ceremonious arrival of the shadowy former Grand Moff Scaven Marx, the notorious 'butcher of Mutanda,' and HM743 tactfully excuses itself. Lynae, recognizing Marx and unafraid, spars verbally with him as he settles uninvited at her table, the two trading veiled barbs about power, monstrousness, and methods. She makes clear she knows exactly who he is and promises to alert Admiral Kizuka to his presence in Caspian space, each leaving the door open to future dealings.",
